@yslbeauty Hyper Luminize Highlighter swatches. I’d initially purchased shades 02 Hypnotic Honey and 03 Rosy Sand but then the gorgeous  cool- toned shade, 69 Lavender Lust, became available and I couldn’t resist.
I love how smooth these look on my skin , shades are pretty too. These are not your typical “beaming” highlighters but rather quite “soft” yet buildable, so I feel “in control” applying them. The Lavender Lust  will work best for me during cooler months while other two shades will work great for me as highlighters/blush toppers all year around. 
The packaging is beautiful and luxurious .
.

And another beautiful highlighter shade from @yslbeauty new Hyper Luminize Highlighter in 69 Lavender Lust.  The shade is very pretty , cool-toned. iI’s a light lavender color highlighter . I love the formula and texture of these new highlighters from #yslbeauty . They have smooth finish with delicate glow that doesn’t accentuate skin imperfections. I actually find it quite forgiving on my skin due to its smoothing effect. Of course, it can be built up to desired intensity, all depends on your preferences.
I’m very happy this shade is currently available in the US.
I will have another post with swatches of all three #yslhyperluminizehighlighter I’ve purchased .
.
@beauty_lux_e #beauty_lux_e .
.

A quick comparison post between new @pradabeauty  Light Glowing Highlighters in 01 and 02 to @yslbeauty Hyper Luminize and @lancomeofficial  Teint Idole highlighters.
I find formulas to be similar across these three brands. Prada in 02 Pink is closest in shade to YSL in 03. I also find that all of these highlighters give similar type of glow and luminosity and same smoothness on my skin. Some of my favorite current formulas besides Dior and Hermes. 
What are your thoughts? I hope you find this comparison helpful.
.

Live swatches of @yslbeauty Couture Mini Clutch Collector Eyeshadow palette in 825 and The Inks Vinyl Cream Collector High Shine Lip Stains in 442 Espresso Kiss and 610 Nude Champion as part of YSL Collector edition .
The packaging is simply beautiful, the color story is very pretty, not revolutionary but perfect for lighter daytime shimmery looks. Plus, I really love #ysleyeshadow formula. Mattes perform great and pink duochrome shade has golden shift to it, very pretty. 
The Lip Stains I personally don’t like but it’s very subjective as I don’t like lip stains in general and I don’t like lip products that have lingering sweet taste. So these are simply not for me , but I have  to admit that they have beautiful satin finish and are long-lasting.
I will post more closeup swatches and my look using this collection.
.
Currently available at @theofficialselfridges .
.
@beauty_lux_e #beauty_lux_e .
.
#ysllipstain #ysllipstains #yslcoutureminiclutchpalette #yslsummermakeupcollection #yslcollectoredition

@pradabeauty Light Glowing  Highlighter Powder in shades 02 Pink and 01 Champagne, and new Light Glowing Lip Oil Sticks in shades Pink, Rose and Brown.
.
The Highlighter Powder is available in three shades and I’ve purchased the two lightest ones. I love both shades I’ve got and a soft glowy finish these add to my skin.  The formula is silky -soft to touch, it blends out beautifully and basically melts into the skin. The glow is soft and not too luminous, perfect for “everyday “ daytime looks. I love both shades I picked. The Pink is a brighter shade while Champagne works great with warmer summer looks. Contains squalane. Refillable packaging and refills can be purchased separately.
.
The Light Glowing Lip Oil Sticks come in sheer shades , that melt into my lips , they are very hydrating , somewhat slippery on lips but are super smoothing at the same time. Light sheer colors and typical for all #pradalipstick scent that I personally love and enjoy ( Infusion D’ris). Also refillable. 
.
I will post more closeup photos and swatch comparisons with other highlighters very soon.
Have you tried any of these?
.

Live swatches of  @diorbeauty new  Dior Backstage Rosy Glow Blush Sticks in shades Toffee, Candy and Rosewood; new Dior Backstage Rosy Glow Powder Blushes and Dior Addict Lip Glow Butter in Toffee and Glazed Lavender. I was simply curious to try these and I was immediately drawn to bright and happy colors of these. I have to say, I’m really happy with the performance .
.
Dior Backstage Rosy Gloe pH-activated Blush Sticks have so many beautiful shades.  The formula is creamy and glowy but not sticky at all. The coverage is buildable and they are long-lasting. They stay on me without fading for 8+ hours. PH-activating technology will make shades and their undertones look slightly different on everyone . I mostly appreciate beautiful shades and glowy finish of these blushes. They have light minty scent to them.
.
Dior Backstage Rosy Glow Powder Blush is slightly more pigmented and maybe just a bit creamier than the previous version, but to be honest, I don’t see  much difference. I’ve used them to set the cream stick blushes and they worked great for that. They blend out well when used alone , and are buildable as well.
.
Dior Addict Lip Butters in Toffee and Glazed Lavender- well, the formulas is great , they feel really nice on lips, are non-sticky and quite nourishing, the finish is beautiful . The packaging is pretty but feels quite light and to me, these are overpriced for this very reason. Again, the formula itself is perfect. 
.

.

Quick comparison swatches of @yslbeauty Couture Mini Clutch Luxury Eyeshadow palettes. Newly released 720 Captivating Dunes compared to 100 Stora Dolls palette and 730 Sunrise Safari compared to palettes in 500 Medina Glow and 200 Gueliz Dream.
To me , all these palettes look different enough to keep them in my collection. Stora Dolls is lighter and slightly warmer than Captivating Dunes palette , and Sunrise Safari pulls more neutral pink when compared to Medina Glow and Gueliz Dream that definitely look warmer, to me at least.
Formula- wise , they all perform really well, and this is one of my favorite eyeshadow formulas.
What are your thoughts? Are you planning to pick any of the newly released palettes ?

@sarah.creal skincare and makeup. It was a long overdue review but I’ve had plenty of time to try all the products and form my opinion on them.
- Moisture Source Brightening Bi-Phase Essence has quickly become my everyday essential  due to it profound moisturizing effect that actually lasts after application. It can be worn on its own or followed by your daily moisturizer. I apply it as my first skincare product after washing my face. It’s almost weightless , has no scent  and does offer some brightening and firming. My combination dry skin loves it.
.
- Firm Offer Eye cream comes is a refillable packaging, it visibly reduces my dark circles and feels quite hydrating . The texture is a bit too thin for my personal preference though.
.
- Brilliant Repair Shield SPF50 in two available shades Vacation and a lighter version, Staycation ( this last shade was gifted by the brand)- is one of my favorite  face spf. It is 100% mineral spf that leaves radiant glowy finish without a white cast. Works really well under my makeup.
.
- The Adults Are Talking serum lip repair in Clarity immediately smoothes and hydrates my normally dry lips. available in tinted versions as well.
.
- Face Flex Concealer and Complexion Enhancer in shades  1,2, 3 and 4 ( shades 3 and 4 were gifted by the brand). This is my favorite product from the brand and one of my favorite concealers . It’s perfect. It’s a high -coverage concealer that doesn’t look heavy at all, doesn’t enhance lines and can be used instead of a foundation. It literally “stretches “ on the face and blends out effortlessly. Full coverage , long- lasting and great shade range. Contains caffeine, green tea and aloe extracts. Totally worth trying. 
The Complexion brush works great with it .
- Speak for Yourself Hydrating Lipstick in Mansplain and Madam President - creamy and hydrating formula and nice colors .
.
-Lip Grip Line Filler is a peptide lip treatment/primer. Has a blurring and gripping qualities and prolongs my lipstick longevity. 
.
@beauty_lux_e #beauty_lux_e  #sarahcrealbeauty #sarahcrealconcealer

latestPosts.caption:
Part of @charlottetilbury Super Nudes Collection are these new Lip Cheat Contour  Duo Lip liners. I wasn’t going to purchase these but #charlottetilburymakeup has kindly sent it to me ( no obligation to post). So I’ve decided to try and review them.
Shown here are shades in Fair, Medium and Tan. So the concept here is to contour your lips with a darker shade and to fill with the lighter one. The formula is nice , very similar to CT Lip Cheat liners.  I love nude colors of these lip pencils and how they allow to shade and contour your lips to make them look fuller. I just personally don’t find them necessary in my collection since I can achieve same effect with almost any lip liner and a bronzer stick in my collection. I guess having these just makes it more convenient. I also don’t feel like each duo has a distinct lighter and darker shades because lighter shades can be easily build up to make them more intense and look just like a deeper shade from the same duo. I hope you can see it from my swatches- when lighter shade is built up , it looks almost identical to a darker shade.
Saying all that, I still like the formula and nude color stories of these making them suitable for almost any lipstick shade. They are very easy to apply and are long lasting.
Have you tried these yet?
.
@beauty_lux_e #beauty_lux_e .

latestPosts.caption:
Lipstick theme continues on my feed. New @westmanatelier Lip Suede Matte Lipstick in Mimi and Lip Shape Lip Liners in Sable, Biscuit and Petal.
.
Mimi lipstick shade described as “tawny beige” and it’s probably the most neutral shade of all of my WA lipsticks . I love shade Mimi in WA blushes and happy to have accompanying lipstick. This is another shade that goes almost with every makeup look.
The formula, just like all #westmanatelierlipstick , is smooth and nourishing , the shade is pretty intense and opaque upon the first swipe( I usually tap these on my lips), it feels like balm on my lips, doesn’t feather though. 
.
New Lip Shape liners are currently available in 8 shades. The formula is very creamy, applies effortlessly and meant to enhance natural lip color. I personally contour my lips with these , fill in and tap them with my finger. And then I tap my lipstick on top. Works great. I find shades to look very natural when applied. Also, on my swatches, both , Sable and Biscuit look very close but on my lips Biscuit is definitely a cool-toned shade whereas Sable is warm-toned .
Very happy with this purchase .
.
I will have a post soon with all of my WA lipsticks swatched , for the reference.
.
@beauty_lux_e #beauty_lux_e .
